You may obtain a copy of the FHIR license at https://www.hl7.org/fhir/license.html.
entry.summary: Healthcare Resource Groups (HRGs) are standard groupings of clinically similar treatments which use comparable levels of healthcare resource. The Health Related Groups 4+ (HRG4+) CodeSystem is a shallow monoaxial classification of around 3000 categories, covering both procedures and diagnoses. The National Casemix Office maps completed episodes of hospital care to an HRG code based partly on the ICD and OPCS codings of that same episode. HRG codes are in turn mapped to the NHS Tarriff in order to determine a standard reimbursement for the episode.
